# ============================================================================
# protect-ssids.conf  —  networks that must NEVER be deauthed
# ============================================================================
# Copy to protect-ssids.conf (setup.sh builds it for you interactively).
# One SSID per line. Trailing '*' = prefix match. '#' starts a comment.
#
# BSSIDs are resolved automatically by wl-refresh (from the recon DB, the
# capture log, and this router's own APs), so you only list SSID NAMES here.
# The generated MAC lists feed both mdk3 (whitelist mode) and hcxdumptool
# (--filtermode=1 protection list).
#
# Examples:
#   MyHomeWiFi            # exact match
#   MyHome*               # protects MyHome, MyHome-5G, MyHome-Guest, ...
#   Office-Corp
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# (add your own networks below — this example ships empty on purpose)
